args: Splendid work on making it through\nthe preliminaries, Your Highness.
It seems like all our daily training paid off.
Lin You may have forced me to enter\nthe tournament, but now that I'm here,\nI want to give it everything I've got.
Keep thrashing fools, and there's no\nlimit to how far you can go!

Er, but what IS the deal with this
tournament, anyway? I thought it was
going to be held in town, but instead
we're out here in the total boonies.
With so many people both participating\nand spectating, there likely isn't an\narena in town that can hold them all.
I prefer it out here, actually; I can just\nfight without worrying about accidentally\ndamaging anything.
You're just upset there are no\nfood carts out here.
What? No! How dare you, madam!
I was watchin' her match earlier, and...
No, I advanced to the next round.\nBut something's going on in the ring\nthat has me concerned.
Probably easier to just show ya. C'mon.
Time has expired! And as the opponent\ndid not show up, the competitor Wu Wei\nis the victor by default!
I take it you have concerns\nabout this Wu Wei person?
He's yet to fight a single battle.
Are you saying he has won ALL of his\nmatches by default? That is unusual\nto say the least.
Yeah, but that ain't all. Check over there.
You're killin' it out there, sir.\nOne more win, and you'll move\non through the preliminaries.
It's the people from before! The ones who\nseized control of that poor man's dojo!
If these people are involved, I retract my\nuse of the word ＂unusual＂ and replace\nit with ＂terrifically suspicious.＂
Oy, boss! I just found out where\nhis next opponent is!
Nice work. ...Ya want us to go\npay 'em a little visit, sir?
It could be some kind of misunderstanding,\nbut we should follow them and make sure.
...Come again, friend? You are demanding\nthat I WITHDRAW from the tournament?
No, no! No one's demandin' nothin'!\nI'm just sayin' it might be best if you\nwere to drop out for your own good, like.
Oh, we got ways to deal with that.\n...Don't we, boys?!
You just can't stop with the cowardice,\ncan you? Especially you, Wu Wei!
How dare you refuse to fight through\nthe tournament on your own merits!\nThat's lower than low!
But since you only seem willing to fight\noutside the ring, I'll take you on right here.\nNOW GET READY TO GET BEAT! YAAAAH!
He dodged Lin You's attack effortlessly!
He's...so strong... And those moves...\nWait, are you—
Tsk. I had hoped for more from you.
If you possessed such prodigious skill,\nto what end did you engage in such\nunderhanded chicanery?
I merely have no desire to grow weaker\nfighting a pack of pathetic nothings.
So instead you CHEAT? There's no way a\nmember of the Qilin tribe would do that!
I've no idea what you think you know about\nthe Qilin tribe, but this is who we are.
We care not for society's notions of good\nor evil, nor the value systems of others.
We strive only to reach greater heights.
That's...exactly what my master said...\nBut he wouldn't... No...
Your master? If you were apprenticed\nto one of the tribe, I am shocked you\ndo not already understand this lesson.
Sh-shut up! You're wrong!\nThe Qilin aren't like that!
Don't you dare say such things!\nAAAAAAAAARGH!
Sloppy skills, muddied by emotion!\nThey are useless against one such as I!
This is poor comedy. I'm leaving now.
It can't be true... It just can't... *sob*
